				\begin{document}$$1.375<|\eta |<3.2$$\end{document}. The central hadronic calorimeter, referred to as the tile calorimeter, uses steel absorber layers interleaved with plastic scintillator covering the pseudorapidity range |η|<1.7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
