In many searches for physics beyond-the-standard model (BSM), including Supersymmetry (SUSY) and other exotic physics signatures, the hard process gives rise to a final state containing energetic jets and a large missing transverse momentum. The selection adopted to discriminate the signal process from the background in such searches typically includes requirements on the ET\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
